    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You weave together threads of shadow to create a sword of solidified gloom in your hand. This magic sword lasts until the spell ends. It counts as a simple melee weapon with which you are proficient. It deals [[/r 2d8]] psychic damage on a hit and has the finesse, light, and thrown properties (range 20/60). In addition, when you use the sword to attack a target that is in dim light or darkness, you make the attack roll with advantage.</p><p>If you drop the weapon or throw it, it dissipates at the end of the turn. Thereafter, while the spell persists, you can use a bonus action to cause the sword to reappear in your hand.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"entry-title-inner\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a 3rd- or 4th-level spell slot, the damage increases to [[/r 3d8]]. When you cast it using a 5th- or 6th-level spell slot, the damage increases to [[/r 4d8]]. When you cast it using a spell slot of 7th level or higher, the damage increases to [[/r 5d8]].</p></div></div>",
